TASK_TITLE=Fix Dashboard ASCII grid — wrong role labels (Subtaskmaster in Core, Worker in Boss)
TASK_STATUS=cancelled
TASK_TYPE=bug
TASK_DESCRIPTION=Two bugs in the Go TUI Dashboard ASCII grid:

1. Core Team window shows 'Subtaskmaster' instead of 'Taskmaster' — the Taskmaster pane (1.0) is being labeled with the wrong role name. The grid is likely reading the role from the wrong source or mapping window 1 panes incorrectly.

2. Dashboard window (window 0) shows 'Boss' AND 'Worker 1' instead of 'Boss' and 'Info Panel'. Pane 0.0 is the Info Panel (shell script, not a Claude instance), pane 0.1 is Boss. The grid is misidentifying 0.0 as a Worker.

The ASCII grid rendering is in tui/internal/model/dashboard.go. Check how it maps pane roles — it should use the actual role from status files or pane metadata, not guess based on pane index. Window 0 = Dashboard (Info Panel + Boss), Window 1 = Core Team (Taskmaster + Task Reviewer + Deployment + Doey Expert).
TASK_SUBTASKS=1:W5.1: Research dashboard.go grid rendering — how pane roles are determined and displayed:done\n2:W5.2: Research status files and role mapping — how roles flow from hooks to TUI:done\n3:W5.1: Implement dashboard.go fixes — key mismatch, roleDisplayNames, window-aware fallbacks:done\n4:W5.2: Verify dashboard.go fixes — build, vet, review correctness:done
